.TH HSH 1 "11 August 2025" "v1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"
.PP
.SH NAME
hsh \-  A minimalist UNIX command-line interpreter written in C
.PP
.SH SYNOPSIS
In interactive mode:
.br
.B ./hsh
.RI [ arguments ]
.PP
In non-interactive mode:
.br
.B echo
.RI [ arguments ]
.B | ./hsh
.PP
.SH DESCRIPTION
A minimalist UNIX command-line interpreter written in C.
It provides a basic environment to execute system commands, similar to the standard sh shell.
It supports both interactive and non-interactive modes.
.PP
.SH BUILTINS
The following built-in commands are supported:
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.
.br
.TP
.B env
Print the current environment variables.
.PP
.SH EXAMPLES
In interactive mode:
.br
.nf
#cisfun$ /bin/ls
AUTHORS  builtin.c  executor.c  hsh  input.c  main.c  man_1_simple_shell  parser.c  path.c  prompt.c  README.md  shell.h  utils.c
.br
#cisfun$ exit
[exit shell]
$
.br
#cisfun$ [Ctrl+D]
[EOF signal: shell exits]
$
.fi
.PP
In non-interactive mode:
.br
.nf
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
AUTHORS  builtin.c  executor.c  hsh  input.c  main.c  man_1_simple_shell  parser.c  path.c  prompt.c  README.md  shell.h  utils.c
.br
$ cat test_ls_2
/bin/ls
/bin/ls
.br
$ cat test_ls_2 | ./hsh
AUTHORS  builtin.c  executor.c  hsh  input.c  main.c  man_1_simple_shell  parser.c  path.c  prompt.c  README.md  shell.h test_ls_2 utils.c
AUTHORS  builtin.c  executor.c  hsh  input.c  main.c  man_1_simple_shell  parser.c  path.c  prompt.c  README.md  shell.h test_ls_2 utils.c
.fi
.PP
